projects:
[{'title': 'NewControl', 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'description': 'ECSEL-2018-2 (Research & Innovation Action)

NewControl overarching goal is to provide an industrially calibrated trajectory towards increased user-acceptance of automated driving control functions, through an approach that is centred on the premise of safety by design. The project aims to develop virtualised platforms for vehicular subsystems that are essential to highly automated driving (realizing functions such as perception, cognition and control), so as to enable mobility-as-a-service for next generation highly automated vehicles.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Zlatan', 'last_name': 'Ajanović', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Roboticist | Researcher in Artificial Intelligence and Robotics | Dr. -Ing'}]}, {'title': 'ITEAM - Interdisciplinary Training Network in Multi-Actuated Ground Vehicles', 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'description': 'ITEAM project is supported by H2020-MSCA-ITN-2015 Marie Sklodowska-Curie Innovative Training Networks grant agreement No 675999.
The main ITEAM target is to establish and sustainably maintain the European training network with the high grade of interdisciplinarity, which will train strong specialists skilled in research and development of novel technologies in the field of multi-actuated ground vehicles.
The global iTEAM goals are:
•	Advance of European postgraduate education in the area of environment- and user-friendly ground vehicle technologies;
•	Reinforcement of cooperation between academia and industry to improve career perspectives of talented graduates in both public and private sectors;
•	Creation of strong European research and innovation group making determinant contributions to next generations of multi-actuated ground vehicles.
The iTEAM project will provide the first-of-its kind European training network in Ground Vehicles at doctorate level to fill up the niche in private sector and industry with researcher-practitioners. The proposed network will be developed as innovative, multidisciplinary, engineering product-oriented and project-based program to train the scientists by integrating cutting-edge research methods of ground vehicles, electric/mechatronic systems, environmental engineering and applied intelligent control.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Zlatan', 'last_name': 'Ajanović', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Roboticist | Researcher in Artificial Intelligence and Robotics | Dr. -Ing'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Valentin', 'last_name': 'Ivanov', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Coordinator of EU Projects | Electric Vehicles | SAE Fellow | European Climate Pact Ambassador'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Daniel', 'last_name': 'Watzenig', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Professor of Automated Driving at TU Graz and Head of Electronics Department at Virtual Vehicle Research'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Stratis', 'last_name': 'Kanarachos', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Branch Director- Coventry University Egypt branch at The Knowledge Hub Universities'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Halil', 'last_name': 'Beglerović', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Research Engineer | Doctor of Technical Sciences'}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Vincenzo', 'last_name': 'Ricciardi, Dr.-Ing.', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Project Manager -
